MOSCOW , September 9 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- A Russian space official said today the crew of the Mir space station has repaired the main on-board computer which failed Monday .
The function of the gyroscopic devices , which keep the station 's solar panels in line with the sun to enable them to generate power , was resumed .
The devices failed Monday after the computer failure .
The cosmonauts are expected to gradually restart the equipment , which had been switched off , and examine and repair parts of the system they depend on for life .
Accidents have frequently occurred on the Mir space station which was established in 1986 .
It has lasted longer than its expected five-year term , and a lack of funds has prevented Russia from setting up new space stations .
About 1,450 failures have reportedly occurred on the Mir in the past 11 years .
